args: You there! Lickspittle! Where are all of\nmy new soldiers?!

I'm afraid we had far fewer volunteers than
we'd hoped for, Your Majesty. Er, and we
also don't appear to have the budget to
increase our armaments either.
Bah! Pathetic! We'll NEVER match\nValkaheim's military prowess at this rate!
But fine. Whatever. Magnus, have we\nreceived any response to our request to\nally with our neighbors?
So they're just IGNORING ME?!\nHow very dare those churls!
Hmm... I wonder what my dear sister\nChelle would do at a time like this?
Begging your pardon, sire, but I wonder\nif perhaps acting in the manner of your\nsiblings might be to your detriment.
You have your own gifts and talents,\nso perhaps it's best you turn to those.
A fact I am very well aware of, thank you!
But one can't rule a country with music and\npaintings, so my prodigious gifts are as\ngood as dirt here!
That's not true at all! Your talents are\njust as precious—

My talents are worth SQUAT in terms of
what we're dealing with now, and that is
the end of it! The only way I can run this
damn place is if I act like one of them...
But you could never become one of them,\nYour Majesty!
M-my deepest apologies if I've spoken out\nof turn, Your Majesty! I meant only—
GET OUT! ALL OF YOU! OUT, OUT, OOOOUT!\nI don't want to see a single one of\nyour ugly mugs around here!
Damn it all. Dammit, dammit, dammit!
They deign to think they know the first\nthing about me?! ME?! EMILE?!
I'm trying everything I possibly can,\nbut I just don't know what to do.
Oh, yes. I thought you might be a king\nof literature, one able to change our\nmilitaristic nation.
Farewell to you, my son. I pray that\nyou become a good and just ruler.
(I know someone said such a thing to me,\nbut I don't remember who.)
What the hell is a king of literature,\nanyway? And how exactly do I become\na ＂good and just＂ ruler?
Who dares intrude? I could have sworn I\ntold the lot of you to get the hell out of\nmy sight!
It is Minister Werner, my liege.\nAnd after such an insolent outburst,\nit is no wonder you flew into a rage.
I have brought the highest quality grape\njuice for you. Please have some and let it\nsoothe your jangled nerves.
You are ever merciful, Your Majesty.\nNow please, do try the grape juice.\nIt is of the finest quality.
I'm glad to see SOMEONE around here has\nsome sense. Give me that. *glug*
Is it not wonderful, Your Majesty?\nI see you are ready to faint dead away\nfrom the deliciousness of it all.
Ah but it is truly the finest quality...\nthe finest quality POISON!

You call yourself an emperor and don't
even bother to test your drink for blight?
Such carelessness truly shows how unfit
you are to lead.
My family served the emperor of the\noriginal Dyrenell Empire.
Which means I am descended from those\nyour pathetic family tore from power.
As heir to the honorable Dyrenell house,\nI am far more worthy of ruling this country\nthan you Alberian filth.
You there! Solider! Throw this rubbish\nin the river where it belongs.
(C-can't stay awake... Is this...the end...\nfor poor Emile...?)
But wait... Am I REALLY alive, or did I die\nback there and end up in some kind of\nterribly dull afterlife?
Yes! You're that teacher from my academy!\nWhat are YOU doing here?!
I found you floating in an estuary while\nswimming on the coast of Saint Lotier.
I hated the thought of your corpse tainting\nthe waters of my beloved sea, so I brought\nyou here instead.
How dare you accuse my beautiful body\nof tainting anything!
Oh, but it would. For you see, having the\nbody of the man who broke our pact in my\nwaters was far too much to bear.
I don't make pacts with teachers, fool!\nUnless... Wait. Wait just one moment...
I mean, I'm clearly just having a laugh\nhere, but, uh, you're not the Waterwyrm\nby some chance, right?
OH, YOU'VE GOTTA BE KIDDING ME!\nI'm taking back the crush I had on you...
I'm sorry, what did you say?
I said nothing! Maybe get your ears\nchecked, you blathering boob!
Oh ho! Someone finally woke up!
Indeed, and thank you again for lending us\nthis fine room.
Hey, you got money, I got rooms.\nSpeaking of which, I assume this gent\nhere is the one who's paying?
Ex-CUSE me? You want ME to pay?\nDon't be absurd! I'm an emperor!
Ha ha! Sure you are, buddy—and I'm the\nking of Grams! ...Here's the bill.
Oh, and if you can't pay, I'll be taking you\nstraight to Lord Zacharias.
And for what possible reason did you take\nme to this urine-soaked hellhole?!\nDo you have ANY idea what I did here?!
Oh, I do. Yet it was a race against time.\nWould you have preferred to die in the\nwaters instead?
Now then, if you don't wish to cause\na scene, I would recommend paying.
Never! Besides, I didn't ask you to save me\nin the first place!
Hmm. It seems we are at an impasse.
Innkeep, if I keep watch of this ingrate,\ncan you call the officials?
NONONONONO WAAAAAAIT!\nThis is a jape, right? A merry jape?\nYou cannot be serious!
Oh, but I am deathly serious. Those who\ncommit crimes must be brought to justice.

Look, if you don't wanna get thrown in the
slammer, just pay up already—and if
you're short of coin, I'm sure you can
find plenty of work here in town.

The idea of ＂work＂ is all well and good for
you, but if I go traipsing about town trying
to employ myself as a scullery wench or
whatnot, they'll simply haul me in anyway!
*sigh* Well, I don't wish to trouble this\npoor innkeep any more than I already\nhave, so it seems I'm stuck.
Emile, be a good boy and wait here.
Well, well! Now THIS is an outfit!
I believe this should be enough to disguise\nyour identity for the time being.
However, do not think you can get away\nwithout paying your dues; Zacharias is\nnot so forgiving as all that.
Grr... Fine, then! If I must work off this\nabsurd debt, then that is what I shall do!
(But can I really do this all by myself?)
